2009 Race Report

A crowd of about 120 competitors turned out to take part in the 2nd Clifden Lifeboat 10k race on sunday 13th September 2009.
Entries came from all over county Galway, as well as Mayo, Cork, Kildare, Dublin, Tyrone as well as 2 from the USA.
The weather was very different from last year, with clear blue skies. This made a challenging course, harder as the temperatures were up into the 20's C by race start at 2pm.


Annette keane 1st woman 2009
Eoin Mullan 1st Male 2009
However this did not put off Eoin Mullan from Tyrone (37.10) and Keith White (37.36) who not only came in 1st and 2nd but also bet last year's best tie of 38.51 mins.

Annette Keane was the 1st woman in (48.33) and younger people also did great time with Liam De coucey coming in first in the under 18's (43.54) and Colm Coneys who at only 12 years of age clocked in at 54.39.



Many thanks to all who took part, those who came out on the way to support them and everyone who helped out or sponsored it in any way.
